invalid: <p>
Based on the posted "original" HTML, you are erroneously attempting to nest an <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> within itself, and you didn't close the <code>&lt;/li&gt;</code> for Schools.  Here is what you posted, but better formatted:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Name: Jordan&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Age: 24&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Schools:
    &lt;ol&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;High School: Anytown Central High&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Colleges:&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;ol&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;NYU&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;Oberlin&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;UCLA&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;/ol&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</pre><p>
Notice that immediately after Colleges: you have a <code>&lt;/li&gt;</code>.  If you remove it, the tag balancing code will properly fix up the remaining errors of 2 unclosed <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> tags.  (Or, you could put the <code>&lt;/li&gt;</code>'s in yourself.)
</p>
<p>
Fixed version looks like:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">&lt;ol&gt;
